{{unreferenced|date=June 2014}} '''Age & Scarpelli''' ({{IPA-it|ˈaːɡe|lang}}) is the [[stage name]] used by the pair of [[Italy|Italian]] [[screenwriter]]s '''[[Agenore Incrocci]]''' (1914–2005) and '''[[Furio Scarpelli]]''' (1919–2010). Together, they wrote the script for about a hundred movies, mainly [[satire|satirical]] [[comedy|comedies]].
The duo started working together in ''[[Totò cerca casa]]'' of [[1949 in film|1949]], and ended their collaboration in the 1980s. They worked for many famous Italian [[film director|directors]], like [[Sergio Leone]] (''[[The Good, the Bad and the Ugly]]''), [[Mario Monicelli]] (including their major work, ''[[L'armata Brancaleone]]''), [[Dino Risi]], [[Luigi Comencini]], [[Pietro Germi]] and [[Ettore Scola]] and they wrote the dialogues of many [[Totò]] movies.
In [[1985 in film|1985]], they decided to part ways, and subsequently worked separately for movies such as ''[[Boom (film)|Boom]]'' for Age and ''[[Il Postino]]'' for Scarpelli.
Age & Scarpelli are often considered the inventors of ''[[commedia all'italiana]]'' (Italian-style comedy).
==Selected filmography== * ''[[Toto Looks For a House]]'' (1949) *''[[47 morto che parla]]'' (1950) * ''[[Toto Looks for a Wife]]'' (1950) * ''[[Toto the Sheik]]'' (1950) * ''[[Figaro Here, Figaro There]]'' (1950) *''[[Totò terzo uomo]]'' (1951) * ''[[Seven Hours of Trouble]]'' (1951) *''[[Totò e le donne]]'' (1952) * ''[[Toto in Color]]'' (1952) * ''[[What Scoundrels Men Are! (1953 film)|What Scoundrels Men Are!]]'' (1953) * ''[[House of Ricordi]]'' (1954) * ''[[Symphony of Love]]'' (1954) *''[[Totò e Carolina]]'' (1955) *''[[Don Camillo|Don Camillo e l'onorevole Peppone]]'' (1955) *''[[La banda degli onesti]]'' (1956) *''[[Il bigamo]]'' (1956) *''[[Big Deal on Madonna Street|I soliti ignoti]]'' (1958) *''[[La legge è legge]]'' (1958) *''[[The Great War (1959 film)|''The Great War'']] (1959) *''[[Audace colpo dei soliti ignoti]]'' (1959) *''[[Everybody Go Home]]'' (1960) * ''[[The Passionate Thief (film)|The Passionate Thief]]'' (1960) *''[[Il mattatore]]'' (1960) *''[[Totò e Peppino divisi a Berlino]]'' (1962) *''[[La marcia su Roma]]'' (1962) *''[[Mafioso (1962 film)|Mafioso]]'' (1962) *''[[Il maestro di Vigevano]]'' (1963) *''[[I compagni]]'' (1963) *''[[I Mostri]]'' (1963) *''[[Seduced and Abandoned]]'' (1964) *''[[L'armata Brancaleone]]'' (1966) *''[[The Good, the Bad and the Ugly|Il buono, il brutto, il cattivo]]'' (1966) *''[[Straziami, ma di baci saziami]]'' (1967) *''[[Brancaleone alle crociate]]'' (1970) *''[[In nome del popolo italiano]]'' (1971) *''[[Romanzo popolare]]'' (1974) *''[[C'eravamo tanto amati]]'' (1974) *''[[La terrazza]]'' (1980)
