{{Infobox recurring event | name = <!--Uses page name if omitted--> | native_name = | logo = File:RECOMB 2018 Logo.png | logo_caption = RECOMB 2018 Logo | image = | imagesize = | caption = RECOMB 2018 Logo | date = | begins = | ends = | prev = RECOMB 2017 | next = RECOMB 2019 | frequency = Annually | location = [[Paris]], [[France]] (2018) | years_active = {{age|1997|01|20}} | first = | last = | participants = | attendance = | genre = | budget = | patron = | organised = [[Ecole Polytechnique]] | people = | member = | website = {{URL|http://recomb2018.fr}} | footnotes = }} '''Research in Computational Molecular Biology''' ('''RECOMB''') is an annual [[academic conference]] on the subjects of [[bioinformatics]] and [[computational biology]]. The conference has been held every year since 1997 and is a major international conference in computational biology, alongside the [[Intelligent Systems for Molecular Biology|ISMB]] and [[European Conference on Computational Biology|ECCB]] conferences.<ref name=eccb-2010-editorial>{{cite journal|last1=Moreau|first1=Y|last2=Heringa|first2=J|title=Yves Moreau and Jaap Heringa, on behalf of the ECCB10 organizing and steering committees.|journal=Bioinformatics|date=Sep 15, 2010|volume=26|issue=18|pages=i412–3|doi=10.1093/bioinformatics/btq482|pmid=20823300|pmc=2935438}}</ref> The conference is affiliated with the [[International Society for Computational Biology]]. Since the first conference, authors of accepted proceedings papers have been invited to submit a revised version to a special issue of the ''[[Journal of Computational Biology]]''.<ref name=jcb-partnership>{{cite web|title=Partnerships|url=http://kdbio.inesc-id.pt/recomb2010/partnership.html|accessdate=8 August 2014|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140809091409/http://kdbio.inesc-id.pt/recomb2010/partnership.html|archivedate=9 August 2014|df=}}</ref>
RECOMB was established in 1997 by Sorin Istrail, [[Pavel Pevzner]] and [[Michael Waterman]]. The first conference was held at the [[Sandia National Laboratories]] in [[Santa Fe, New Mexico]].<ref name=recomb2014-proceedings />
A series of RECOMB Satellite meetings was established by [[Pavel Pevzner]] in 2001. These meetings cover specialist aspects of bioinformatics, including [[massively parallel sequencing]], [[comparative genomics]], [[Regulation of gene expression|regulatory genomics]] and bioinformatics education.<ref name=satellites>{{cite web|title=RECOMB - Annual International Conference on Research in Computational Molecular Biology - History - RECOMB Satellite Workshops|url=http://www.recomb.org/22481/RECOMB-Satellite-Workshops|accessdate=9 August 2014}}</ref>
As of RECOMB 2010, the conference has included a highlights track, modelled on the success of a similar track at the ISMB conference. The highlights track contains presentations for computational biology papers published in the previous 18 months.<ref name=recomb2014-proceedings /><ref name=recomb-2010-highlights>{{cite web|title=RECOMB 2010 - Highlights Track|url=http://kdbio.inesc-id.pt/recomb2010/highlights.html|accessdate=11 August 2014|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110323003759/http://kdbio.inesc-id.pt/recomb2010/highlights.html|archivedate=23 March 2011|df=}}</ref>
In 2014 RECOMB and ''[[PLOS Computational Biology]]'' coordinated to let authors submit papers in parallel to both conference and journal. Papers not selected for publication in ''PLOS Computational Biology'' were published in edited form in the ''Journal of Computational Biology'' as usual.<ref name=recomb2014-proceedings /><ref name=plos-biologue>{{cite web|title=The Pick of RECOMB 2014 - PLOS Biologue|url=http://blogs.plos.org/biologue/2014/03/27/pick-recomb-2014/|website=http://blogs.plos.org|publisher=PLOS|accessdate=11 August 2014|date=2014-03-27}}</ref>
